In this HTML and CSS code, I have tried to make a website using the same which tells about:
1. how people can connect me.
2. why people should connect me.
3. about me and my skills.
It is just how much I know and till date how much have I done.

# Project Structure:-
The `<html>` tag contains the complete structure of the website.

-<head> section includes:
<title> tag – Displays "Jahan | Portfolio" on the browser tab.
  <link> tag – Connects the external CSS file (`style.css`) for styling.
<body> contains all visible content of the webpage.

Displays the name using `<h1>`
Shows a tagline using `<p>`
Styled with a gradient background
Text is centered using Flexbox

Navigation Bar Contains:
  - About
  - Skills
  - Projects
  - Contact
Uses smooth scrolling
Includes hover effects for better user interaction

# CSS Styling Features

The CSS file is responsible for:

- Setting background color and font style
- Applying spacing and layout alignment
- Creating a gradient header background
- Using Flexbox for layout design
- Adding hover effects for navigation links and cards
- Creating modern glass-like design effects using `backdrop-filter`
- Enabling smooth scrolling using `scroll-behavior`
